IRS990.MissionDesc: SET THE STANDARD FOR EXCELLENCE IN THE DELIVERY OF HOME CARE SERVICE TO THE CITIZENS OF SOUTHEAST MISSOURI THROUGH THERAPEUTIC, CUSTODIAL, PALLIATIVE AND PREVENTIVE CARE.
IRS990.Desc: IN-HOME SERVICES SERVED 651 CLIENTS IN FISCAL YEAR 2018 AND DELIVERED 260,145 HOURS OF CARE. THIS PROGRAM SERVES PRIMARILY MEDICAID RECIPIENTS WHO RECEIVE CARE IN THEIR HOME. SERVICES PROVIDED INCLUDE BASIC HOUSEKEEPING, ASSISTANCE WITH PERSONAL HYGIENE, LAUNDRY, ESSENTIAL ERRANDS, MAINTENANCE HEALTH CARE NEEDS, AND RESPITE CARE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: HOME HEALTH SERVED 1,332 CLIENTS IN FISCAL YEAR 2018 AND DELIVERED 22,022 VISITS. THIS PROGRAM SERVES HOME BOUND PATIENTS WITH A SKILLED NEED. RNS, LPNS, THERAPISTS AND AIDES PROVIDE PROFESSIONAL SERVICES TO PATIENTS IN THE PRIVACY OF THEIR OWN HOME UNDER DIRECT ORDERS FROM THE PRIVATE PHYSICIAN.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: HOSPICE SERVED 245 PATIENTS IN FISCAL YEAR 2018 AND DELIVERED 14,134 DAYS OF CARE. HOSPICE SERVICES ARE PROVIDED TO SUPPORT AND COMFORT DYING PATIENTS AND THEIR FAMILIES. THIS COMPREHENSIVE PROGRAM, PROVIDED BY PHYSICIANS, NURSES, COUNSELORS AND OTHER PROFESSIONALS, IS DESIGNED TO KEEP THE PATIENT COMFORTABLE AND ALERT AT HOME WHILE EMOTIONAL SUPPORT IS GIVEN TO ALL FAMILY MEMBERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: OTHER LOBBYING ACTIVITIES: THE ORGANIZATION PAYS ANNUAL DUES TO THE MISSOURI ALLIANCE FOR HOME CARE AND THE MISSOURI HOSPICE AND PALLIATIVE CARE ASSOCIATION. A PORTION OF THESE DUES IS ATTRIBUTABLE TO LOBBYING PURPOSES.

ESCROW AND CUSTODIAL ARRANGEMENTS: THE ORGANIZATION HAS A CHRISTMAS CLUB THAT ALLOWS EMPLOYEES TO ELECT TO HAVE A CERTAIN AMOUNT WITHHELD FROM EACH PAYCHECK. NO ADDITIONAL CONTRIBUTIONS ARE MADE BY THE ORGANIZATION. THE ACCOUNT IS DISTRIBUTED TO THE EMPLOYEES EACH OCTOBER.

UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS: MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THEIR INCOME TAX POSITIONS UNDER THE GUIDANCE INCLUDED IN ASC 740. BASED ON THEIR REVIEW, MANAGEMENT HAS NOT IDENTIFIED ANY MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS TO BE RECORDED OR DISCLOSED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.
AMOUNTS INCLUDED ON FORM 990, PART VIII, LINE 12, BUT NOT ON LINE 1: $ 25,983 GAIN ON DISPOSAL OF PROPERTY
AMOUNTS INCLUDED ON LINE 1 BUT NOT ON FORM 990, PART IX, LINE 25: $ (25,983) GAIN ON DISPOSAL OF PROPERTY
NON-FIXED PAYMENTS: EMPLOYEES RECEIVED CHRISTMAS BONUSES AND YEAR END BONUSES, INCLUDING OFFICERS.

ORGANIZATION'S MISSION: THE MISSION OF THE VISITING NURSE ASSOCIATION OF SOUTHEAST MISSOURI, INC. IS TO SET THE STANDARD FOR EXCELLENCE IN THE DELIVERY OF HOME CARE SERVICE TO THE CITIZENS OF SOUTHEAST MISSOURI THROUGH THERAPEUTIC, CUSTODIAL, PALLIATIVE, AND PREVENTIVE CARE IN A COOPERATIVE AND SEAMLESS SYSTEM, UTILIZING INNOVATION, DIVERSIFICATION AND COST EFFECTIVE METHODS IN AN ENVIRONMENT THAT FOSTERS LEARNING AND DEMONSTRATES POSITIVE OUTCOMES. THE SERVICES WILL BE PROVIDED WITHOUT REGARD TO AGE, RACE, CREED, DISABILITY, OR ECONOMIC STATUS. THE MISSION WILL BE CARRIED OUT USING THE NOT FOR PROFIT CORPORATION FORM OF DOING BUSINESS AS DEFINED IN CHAPTER 355 OF THE REVISED STATUTES OF MISSOURI.

OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES: CONSUMER DIRECTED SERVICES (CDS) SERVED 107 CONSUMERS IN FISCAL YEAR 2018 AND DELIVERED 77,009 HOURS. CONSUMER DIRECTED SERVICES (CDS) ENABLES PHYSICALLY DISABLED INDIVIDUALS TO CONTINUE TO LIVE INDEPENDENTLY WITHIN THEIR OWN HOME RATHER THAN GOING TO A NURSING FACILITY. CDS EMPOWERS THE CONSUMER TO REMAIN IN CONTROL OF THEIR LIVES BY GIVING THEM THE FREEDOM TO CHOOSE THEIR OWN CAREGIVER. PRIVATE DUTY SERVED 34 PATIENTS IN FISCAL YEAR 2018 AND DELIVERED 65,574 HOURS. PRIVATE DUTY SERVICE IS PROVIDED WHEN NURSING CARE IS NEEDED FOR MORE THAN WHAT CAN BE PROVIDED IN AN INTERMITTENT HOME HEALTH VISIT AND THE PATIENT STILL PREFERS TO RECOVER AT HOME. RNS AND LPNS PROVIDE SKILLED AND NON-SKILLED SERVICES FOR ONE PATIENT OVER A PRE-SET PERIOD OF TIME CALLED A SHIFT. THE AMOUNT OF HOURS PROVIDED DEPENDS ON THE NEEDS OF THE PATIENT. DURABLE MEDICAL EQUIPMENT PROVIDES EQUIPMENT NEEDS TO KEEP PATIENTS SAFE AND COMFORTABLE IN THEIR HOMES. SENIOR COMPANION SERVICES ARE FUNDED IN PART BY A FEDERAL GRANT AND ALLOWS SENIORS TO PROVIDE ASSISTANCE TO SENIORS LIVING AT HOME.
AUTHORITY DELEGATED TO EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE: EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE CAN VOTE UNANIMOUSLY TO MAKE A DECISION ON BEHALF OF THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: REVIEW OF FORM 990: THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM BASED ON THE AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND INFORMATION PROVIDED BY THE ACCOUNTING DEPARTMENT OF THE ORGANIZATION. THE CEO AND CFO COMPLETE A THOROUGH REVIEW OF THE 990. THE RETURN IS THEN PRESENTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS WHO HAVE AN OPPORTUNITY TO ASK QUESTIONS OR MAKE COMMENTS BEFORE THE RETURN IS FILED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MONITORING COMPLIANCE WITH CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY: CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ANNUAL DISCLOSURES ARE REVIEWED BY THE COMPLIANCE OFFICER. ANY CONFLICTS ARE REVIEWED BY THE CEO AND REPORTED TO THE BOARD ANNUALLY. BOARD MEMBERS WITH POTENTIAL CONFLICTS ABSTAIN FROM VOTING ON ITEMS RELATED TO THAT CONFLICT. CORPORATE OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES ARE ALSO REQUIRED TO ANNUALLY DISCLOSE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A & 15B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION DETERMINATION: THE FINANCE/BUDGET COMMITTEE MEETING WAS HELD ON 5/31/2018 AND BUDGET ITEMS WERE DISCUSSED IN DETAIL INCLUDING PAYROLL. PAY INCREASES OF UP TO 3% WERE DISCUSSED AND APPROVED TO CONTINUE FOR THE NEW BUDGETED FISCAL YEAR 2019. AFTER THE MEETING AN EMAIL WAS SENT TO COMMITTEE MEMBERS WITH MANAGEMENT SALARY COMPARISON INFORMATION. THE COMMITTEE REVIEWED THE INFORMATION PRIOR TO THE 6/28/2018 BOARD MEETING AND MADE A RECOMMENDATION TO THE BOARD AT THE MEETING FOR SALARIES FOR CEO AND CFO.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DOCUMENT DISCLOSURE: THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE ALL AVAILABLE TO BE VIEWED AT THE ORGANIZATION'S PLACE OF BUSINESS UPON WRITTEN REQUEST.
